highlights.description: There is something magical about whatever it is that they're doing in my kids' school
We make a day of taking our boat around Lake Mendota, to the locks to the other lakes
Ice fishing is a way to be out in the fresh air and sunshine
Uneasiness with a neighborhood watch program that is looking for people who don't belong
We need to learn to cooperate and throw in together, from people in different school systems to nonprofits
Teacher struggling with playing the role of educator and social worker
Where can I live that has access to public transportation so an Uber to a doctor's appointment doesn't cost $45?

Amparo tells the story of a young Black girl getting pushed by principle and her hair pulled. No accountability was shown. Amparo asks: "What does that tell this young little girl? That her experience is not valid? That she is now a victim and nobody believes you? You have no voice. There is no justice for you?"
